# History: testing-deterministic-clock-vs-thread-sleep-classification

This file preserves prior versions of the canonical skill body.

## v2.0.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1469 / PR #1725 — IMPLEMENTATION of the sleep
removal (the v1.x versions were plan-only, unverified).
**Verification:** verified-local (23 status_tracker + 35 circuit_breaker tests green ×3 runs
locally; ruff clean; CI on PR #1725 pending at capture time).

### What changed

- **Reversed the Class-2 (thread-coordination) core recommendation.** v1.x recommended
  `@pytest.mark.slow` to deselect thread-coordination sleeps on the fast path. A reviewer
  REJECTED that: quarantining behind `slow` removes the wait/notify code under test from
  the default fast CI suite (reducing coverage of the very logic) AND leaves the underlying
  flakiness intact. The new core fix is **deterministic Event-based coordination** —
  instrument `condition.wait` to set a `threading.Event` from inside the lock right before
  parking, so the releaser provably runs happens-after.
- Verification level promoted `unverified` → `verified-local`; Overview/Outcome rewritten
  from "planning hypothesis, no code written" to the verified implementation results.
- Added the **failure-time-stamp ordering** insight: advance the mocked clock AFTER the
  failing call returns, not at construction, because `_record_failure` stamps
  `_last_failure_time = time.monotonic()` at failure time.
- Added a third sleep class — **pure-contention "simulate work" sleeps** — whose fix is
  simply to DELETE the sleep.
- Added the mocked-clock-across-threads safety reasoning (frozen MagicMock read is
  thread-safe because those tests assert on state/counters, never elapsed/ETA time).
- Removed the plan-only framing (title, "Proposed Workflow (UNVERIFIED)" warning,
  "Most-uncertain assumptions" risk table, plan-artifact-discipline pipeline note — that
  process learning lives in its own dedicated skill space and was specific to the planning
  rounds). Header restored to plain `## Verified Workflow`.
- Tag set updated: dropped `pytest-mark-slow`, `planning`, `plan-review-pipeline`,
  `plan-artifact-discipline`, `mechanically-derived-count`, `threading-barrier`; added
  `threading-event`, `condition-wait-instrumentation`, `happens-before`, `kiss`.

### Why

v1.x was captured at the planning stage and recommended the low-risk-but-wrong `slow`
marker. Implementation review showed the marker is the anti-pattern; the deterministic
Event-instrumentation technique is what actually converged the review and removed the
flakiness without dropping coverage. Because this changes the core recommendation and the
verification level, it is a MAJOR bump.

