## v1.1.0 (2026-06-30)

Added a PLAN-PROCESS failure mode observed across the issue #1469 re-planning rounds: in a TASK/PLAN/REVIEW pipeline where the plan reviewer only sees the latest emitted artifact, the plan author MUST output the COMPLETE plan inline every round. Pointing to "the full plan in my prior message" or emitting a `/learn`-completion / status report in the plan slot makes the reviewed artifact contain NO plan → automatic NOGO/F regardless of how correct the off-artifact plan was (R1 went F purely for this). Re-confirmed the mechanically-derived-count rule (6 sleeps across 5 methods; assert `pytest -m slow --collect-only -q | grep -c "::"` == 5) as the substantive fix that converged the plan after the "3 vs 4 vs 5" oscillation. Added two Failed Attempts rows and a "Plan-artifact discipline" note to the workflow.

